{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"90dbe1b0-6847-4a7e-b121-94897a87205e","content":"I can help guide you on analyzing your .dmp file! Note: the `dump-collect` skill I have available is only for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them. But here's how to investigate your crash dump:\n\n### Tools for Analysis\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Useful commands inside the REPL:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack\n   - `pe` — print last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n\n2. **LLDB + SOS** (Linux):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-sos install\n   lldb --core your-file.dmp\n   ```\n\n3. **WinDbg** (Windows) — best for full native + managed analysis.\n\n### Quick Triage Steps\n\n1. Run `dotnet-dump analyze <file>` and type **`pe`** to print the exception that caused the crash.\n2. Use **`clrstack`** to see the managed stack trace.\n3. Check **`threads`** to see if multiple threads were involved.\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and run the analysis on your file? If so, let me know the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b3180bfc-ca7d-47a9-976f-eb383f6a367d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for configuring and collecting crash dumps, and explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":449,"requestId":"1B86:2BCA1C:16D2469:198C6E3:6A02882C"},"id":"d42979ec-0431-4ce1-b397-647e6ca91667","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:54:00.724Z","parentId":"f35910a4-b8c5-45e0-b70e-e6c288981cef"}
